<div class="p-6 bg-white rounded font-sans text-gray-800 space-y-8">
  <p class="leading-normal">
    A <strong>stem</strong> is the intermediate form of a word between the <em>lemma</em> and its inflected surface form. It typically reflects the base pattern of a word before it’s conjugated or declined. Stemming is used in linguistic processing to group words with similar forms.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-green-100 border border-green-300 text-green-800 px-4 py-3 rounded" role="alert">
    <p class="font-semibold">ℹ️ Note:</p>
    <p class="leading-normal">
      While a <strong>lemma</strong> is a dictionary entry (e.g., <span class="font-mono">رَحِمَ</span>), a <strong>stem</strong> may be a simplified, reduced form (e.g., <span class="font-mono">رَحْم</span>) used for grouping variants. It may not always correspond to a valid Arabic word.
    </p>

    <p class="leading-normal">
      Stemming is useful for grouping words in search, clustering, or analyzing morphological variation without needing the full lemma or root system.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 border-l-4 border-gray-300 p-4">
    <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Example:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
      <li>
        Lemma: <span class="font-mono bg-gray-100 px-1">رَحِمَ</span> – to have mercy
      </li>
      <li>
        Stem: <span class="font-mono bg-gray-100 px-1">رَحْم</span>
      </li>
      <li>Related forms:
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-1 space-y-1">
          <li><span class="qpc-hafs font-bold">رَحْمَة</span> (raḥmah) – mercy</li>
          <li><span class="qpc-hafs font-bold">يَرْحَمُ</span> (yarḥamu) – he shows mercy</li>
          <li><span class="qpc-hafs font-bold">الرَّحِيم</span> (Ar-Raḥīm) – the Merciful</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div>
    <p class="leading-normal">
      QUL exports stem data in the <code class="font-mono">stems</code> and <code class="font-mono">word_stems</code> tables of the SQLite dataset.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-4">
      <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Table: <code class="font-mono">stems</code></h4>
      <table class="w-full table-auto border-collapse text-sm">
        <thead class="bg-gray-100 text-gray-700">
        <tr>
          <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Column</th>
          <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Type</th>
          <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Description</th>
        </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
          <td class="px-4 py-2">id</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-2">INTEGER</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-2">Unique identifier for the stem</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 bg-gray-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-2">text</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-2">TEXT</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-2">Stem text with tashkeel</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
          <td class="px-4 py-2">text_clean</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-2">TEXT</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-2">Stem text without tashkeel</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 bg-gray-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-2">words_count</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-2">INTEGER</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-2">Total occurrences of all derived words for stem</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
          <td class="px-4 py-2">uniq_words_count</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-2">INTEGER</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-2">Count of unique word forms derived from this stem</td>
        </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6">
      <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Table: <code class="font-mono">word_stems</code></h4>
      <table class="w-full table-auto border-collapse text-sm">
        <thead class="bg-gray-100 text-gray-700">
        <tr>
          <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Column</th>
          <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Type</th>
          <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Description</th>
        </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
          <td class="px-4 py-2">stem_id</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-2">INTEGER</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-2">Foreign key to <code class="font-mono">stems.id</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
          <td class="px-4 py-2">location</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-2">TEXT</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-2">Word location (e.g. <code>1:1:2</code>)</td>
        </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
